# LiveMask CI/CD - AI Development Rules v3.7

## TASK-CICD-WORKSPACE-PATH-MIGRATION-001 — Workspace Path Rule

### Mandatory Workspace Pre-Check
Before any development, output the following and verify:

```bash
pwd
git remote -v
git branch --show-current
git status --short
```

### Banned Old Path
If `pwd` begins with `/Users/sammytan/Documents/New project 2`, the AI **must stop immediately**.
Do not edit files, do not commit, do not merge. Report:

```text
BLOCKED: Old workspace path detected.
pwd: <current-pwd>
This window must be reopened from /Users/sammytan/Developer/LiveMask/<repo>.
No files changed.
```

### Default Workspace Root
- Workspace root is `/Users/sammytan/Developer/LiveMask`.
- Scripts should prefer `"${LIVEMASK_WORKSPACE_ROOT:-$HOME/Developer/LiveMask}"`.
- Do not hardcode `/Users/sammytan/Documents/New project 2` anywhere in this repo.
- Do not hardcode `/Users/sammytan/Developer/LiveMask` directly when `LIVEMASK_WORKSPACE_ROOT` is available.
- Runtime repos must not update `livemask-docs` task ledgers directly.

